mintty
------------------------------------------
MinTTY is a terminal emulator for Cygwin. It is based on code from 
PuTTY 0.60 by Simon Tatham and team.

Features include:
* Xterm-compatible terminal emulation.
* Native Windows user interface that tries to keep things simple.
* Unicode support, not limited to the Basic Multilingual Plane
* Drag & drop and copy & paste of text, files and folders. 
* Options are stored in a text file. No registry entries.
* Window transparency.
* Small executable size (currently <120K). 

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-62

Build requirements:
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.4-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1
  w32api-3.12-1

Canonical website:
  http://mintty.googlecode.com

Canonical download:
  http://code.google.com/p/mintty/downloads/list

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack mintty-0.5.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
    unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./mintty-0.5.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mintty-0.5.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/mintty-0.5.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/postinstall/mintty.sh
  /etc/preremove/mintty.sh
  /usr/bin/mintty.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mintty-0.5.1.README
  /usr/share/doc/mintty-0.5.1/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/mintty-0.5.1/LICENSE.Oxygen
  /usr/share/doc/mintty-0.5.1/LICENSE.PuTTY
  /usr/share/man/man1/mintty.1.gz

------------------

Port Notes:

----- mintty-0.5.1-1 -----
* Added options for configuring Cygwin 1.7's locales.
* Unicode support beyond the Basic Multilingual Plane.
* Ctrl+click opening of files, folders, links.
* Changed backspace key default to ^?.

----- mintty-0.4.4-1 -----
* Tweaks and compatibility fixes.

----- mintty-0.4.3-1 -----
* Skipping Windows 7 popup console workaround on Cygwin API >= 0.211.
* Improved versioning.
* Enhancements: custom icon, aplication escape key mode, DECSCUSR.

----- mintty-0.4.2-1 -----
* Fixed bug that meant that codepage setting was ignored on output.
* Removed C1 control character processing.
* Various smaller fixes and improvements to the man page.

----- mintty-0.4.1-1 -----
* Spit'n'polish

----- mintty-0.4.0-2 -----
* Postinstall and preremove scripts were missing.

----- mintty-0.4.0-1 -----
* Revamped options dialog with added Apply button.
* Better keyboard handling, including xterm modifyOtherKeys mode.
* Added --log and --hold options.
* Lots of little fixes.

----- mintty-0.3.10-1 -----
* Fixed a couple of codepage and font handling bugs introduced in 0.3.10.

----- mintty-0.3.9-1 -----
* Improved support for East Asian languages.
* Workaround for Windows 7 console popups.

----- mintty-0.3.8-1 -----
* Added -e option and duplicate command.

----- mintty-0.3.7-1 -----
* Quick respin to address a couple of xterm incompatibilities.

----- mintty-0.3.6-1 -----
* Update to version 0.3.6. 
* Replaced readme.html with manual page. Thanks to Lee D. Rothstein for 
helping with that.

----- mintty-0.3.5-1 -----
* First attempt at Cygwin setup package. Thanks to Yaakov Selkovitz for 
getting this off the ground by adding MinTTY to Cygports.

Cygwin port maintained by:  Andy Koppe  cygwin@cygwin.com
Please address questions to the Cygwin mailing list at 
<cygwin@cygwin.com> or to the MinTTY discussion group at
http://groups.google.com/group/mintty-discuss.
